Class SampleDataGalleryActivity

java.lang.Object
  Activity
      com.vasova.bachelorproject.SampleDataGalleryActivity

public class SampleDataGalleryActivity
extends Activity

Activity for browsing sample images. This activity is used to view thumbnails of the sample input images for this application and enables user to select individual items.

update3DData

public static void update3DData(float[] v,
                                float[] c)
This method updates the data for 3D visualization.

Parameters:
v - an array of vertices, each three items represents one vertex as the coordinates x, y and z, each nine items one triangle.
c - an array of colors, one color is assigned to one vertex in the v array. Each four items represents one color with the RGBA values.

getVerticesFor3DVisualization

public static float[] getVerticesFor3DVisualization()
This synchronized method returns an array of vertices ready for 3D visualization.

Returns:
Returns an array of floats, each three items of the array represent one vertex for 3D reconstruction.

getColorsFor3DVisualization

public static float[] getColorsFor3DVisualization()
This synchronized method returns an array of colors ready for 3D visualization.

Returns:
Returns an array of colors for 3D reconstruction, each four items of the array represent one RGBA color.

areNew3DDataAvailable

public static boolean areNew3DDataAvailable()
This synchronized method returns true if there are new data for 3D visualization update or false if are not.

Returns:
Returns true (if there are new vertices and colors to 3D visualization) or false (if the arrays of vertices and colors have not changed).

update2DData

public static void update2DData(org.opencv.core.Mat m)
This method sets a Mat as the image for visualization and true as a notification of new available data.

Parameters:
m - Mat for 2D visualization. The type of the Mat needs be the CvType.CV_8UC3 type.

getImgForVisualization

public static org.opencv.core.Mat getImgForVisualization()
This synchronized method returns an image as a Mat that should be visualized. Type of the matrix is CvType.CV_8UC3.

Returns:
Returns Mat of CvType.CV_8UC3 type.

areNew2DDataAvailable

public static boolean areNew2DDataAvailable()
This synchronized method returns a true if there is new image for visualization or false if is not.

Returns:
Returns true (if there is new Mat for 2D visualization) or false (if Mat have not changed).
